1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,368
There is a reason why the you are unimportant attitude prevails.

2
00:00:04,639 --> 00:00:11,328
Most folks look at another person and think, he can't do anything for me, therefore he's not important.

3
00:00:11,598 --> 00:00:15,169
But right there is where people make a basic blunder.

4
00:00:15,439 --> 00:00:20,848
The other person, regardless of his status or his income, is important to you,

5
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:24,289
and for two giant dollars and cents reasons.

6
00:00:24,879 --> 00:00:29,730
First, people do more for you when you make them feel important.

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,529
Years ago, in Detroit, I rode a certain bus to work each morning.

8
00:00:34,639 --> 00:00:36,689
The driver was an old grump.

9
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:43,888
Dozens, maybe hundreds of times, I saw this driver pull away from the curb when a wildly waving,

10
00:00:43,919 --> 00:00:48,128
shouting, and running passenger was just a second or two from the door.

11
00:00:48,639 --> 00:00:55,328
Over a period of several months, I saw this driver show special courtesy to only one passenger,

12
00:00:55,439 --> 00:00:59,328
and this passenger was shown special courtesy many times.

13
00:00:59,598 --> 00:01:02,368
The driver would wait for this passenger.

14
00:01:02,559 --> 00:01:03,490
And why?

15
00:01:03,759 --> 00:01:08,769
Because this passenger went out of his way to make the driver feel important.

16
00:01:09,119 --> 00:01:14,769
Every morning he greeted the driver with a personalized, sincere, good morning, sir.

17
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:22,450
Sometimes this passenger would sit near the driver and make little comments like, you sure have a lot of responsibility.

18
00:01:22,639 --> 00:01:26,929
It must take nerves of steel to drive through traffic like this every day.

19
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,569
You sure keep this thing on schedule.

20
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:37,730
That passenger made the driver feel as important as if he were piloting a 180-passenger jet airliner.

21
00:01:37,838 --> 00:01:42,210
And the driver, in return, showed special courtesy to the passenger.

22
00:01:42,879 --> 00:01:46,769
It pays to make little people feel like big people.

23
00:01:47,359 --> 00:01:55,250
Today, in thousands of offices all over America, secretaries are helping salesmen make sales or lose sales,

24
00:01:55,359 --> 00:01:57,888
depending on how the salesman has treated them.

25
00:01:58,240 --> 00:02:01,409
Make someone feel important and he cares about you.

26
00:02:01,519 --> 00:02:05,088
And when he cares about you, he does more for you.

27
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,289
Customers will buy more from you.

28
00:02:08,399 --> 00:02:10,608
Employees will work harder for you.

29
00:02:10,799 --> 00:02:14,128
Associates will go out of their way to cooperate with you.

30
00:02:14,159 --> 00:02:19,730
Your boss will do more to help you, if you will only make these people feel important.

31
00:02:20,559 --> 00:02:23,730
It pays to make big people feel even bigger.

32
00:02:23,919 --> 00:02:29,409
The big thinker always adds value to people by visualizing them at their best.

33
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:34,210
Because he thinks big about people, he gets their best out of them.

34
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:40,210
Here's the second giant reason for making others feel important.

